# .easignore — what EAS Build should exclude from the upload tarball.
# Syntax is the same as .gitignore.
#
# GOTCHA: patterns without a leading "/" match ANY directory with that name
# anywhere in the tree. So `tools/` (without slash) would also match
# `src/features/tools/` and break the JS bundle. Always anchor repo-root
# directories with a leading slash (e.g. `/_archive/`, `/docs/`) and reserve
# globs like `**/foo/` for things you really want recursively excluded.
#
# Issue #555 tracks the history of this file (first version shipped bare
# `tools/` and broke the first APK build).

# Repo-root heavy directories (anchored — see gotcha above)
/.git/
/_archive/
/docs/
/tools/
/.github/
/.claude/
/.codex
/*.pdf

# Sibling monorepo packages — irrelevant for the mobile-app build
/packages/api/
/packages/website/
/packages/beer-encyclopedia/

# Dependencies — EAS reinstalls on its servers from the lockfile
node_modules/

# Python / ML environments possibly present under sibling packages
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/__pycache__/

# Local prebuild output — keep the build on the managed workflow (continuous
# native generation), matching the May 2026 APKs. These dirs are gitignored
# local artifacts; uploading them flips EAS into the bare workflow and breaks
# the appVersion runtimeVersion policy. Anchored to the package root.
/android/
/ios/

# Local artifacts (can appear in either workspace or package)
.expo/
coverage/
dist/
build/
*.log
*.tar.gz
*.zip

# IDE / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
